300 1455 M
(Title:)t
450 1455 M
(         Relational operator templates)t
300 1495 M
(Section:       20.2.1 [)t
829 1495 M
(lib.operators])t
300 1535 M
(Status:        Open)t
300 1615 M
(Note:          Treated as a Clause 17 issue due to wide impact.)t
300 1695 M
(Description:)t
450 1775 M
(The STL provides a set of templates defining the equality and)t
450 1815 M
(inequality operators in terms of other operators in the set. The)t
450 1855 M
(intention is that people defining their own classes to be used with the)t
450 1895 M
(STL have to provide only some of the necessary operators, and the)t
450 1935 M
(others will be "magically" provided. Currently, it is practically)t
450 1975 M
(impossible to avoid having these operator templates apply to user)t
450 2015 M
(written classes, even when they are not appropriate.)t
450 2095 M
(There are two obvious solutions to the problem. One is to remove the)t
450 2135 M
(template operators altogether. The other is to put them in a namespace)t
450 2175 M
(of their own. I believe that for this to work, no standard namespace)t
450 2215 M
(should "use" this new namespace, or the operators will once again leak)t
450 2255 M
(out, but I need to think further about this. The ")t
1600 2255 M
(Koenig lookup rule")t
450 2295 M
(and the transitive lookup rules we've added recently seem to make it)t
450 2335 M
(harder to keep these operators under control, but I'm not sure.)t
300 2415 M
(Resolution:)t
300 2495 M
(Requestor:     United Kingdom)t
300 2535 M
(Owner:         Steve )t
783 2535 M
(Rumsby)t
300 2575 M
(Emails:)t
300 2615 M
(Papers:        95-0170 = N0770 UK Comments Issue #135)t
