(<---------------------------------------------------------------------->)t
300 1516 M
(Work Group:    Library Clause 17)t
300 1556 M
(Issue Number:  17-010)t
300 1596 M
(Title:)t
450 1596 M
(         Too Many Classes and Features in Standard Library)t
300 1636 M
(Section:)t
300 1676 M
(Status:        Open)t
300 1716 M
(Description:)t
450 1796 M
(The standard library contains far too many classes and features.  It is)t
450 1836 M
(clear that C++ \(like C\) needs a standard library.  The reason for this)t
450 1876 M
(is that the language itself has no method for communication with the)t
450 1916 M
(system \(I/O, date/time and other system dependencies\). A standard)t
450 1956 M
(library for these system-dependent features is necessary to allow)t
450 1996 M
(portable code to be written.  The C standard was focused upon these)t
450 2036 M
(issues, however the proposed C++ standard library introduces many)t
450 2076 M
(classes and features \(in particular standard data structures and)t
450 2116 M
(algorithms\) that do not add to the portability of the language.)t
450 2196 M
(This is not to say that it would not be nice to have standard)t
450 2236 M
(definitions for these features, but it should not be part of the C++)t
450 2276 M
(language standard.  Adding these features to the CV++ standard)t
450 2316 M
(complicates both the implementation \(e.g. for embedded systems\) and the)t
450 2356 M
(learning of the language.  Furthermore, it is not clear at the moment)t
450 2396 M
(whether the features included in the library are really what is needed.)t
450 2436 M
(In fact, if one considers the currently available commercial libraries)t
450 2476 M
(as an indication. There is much more need for a standard library for)t
