300 975 M
(Work Group:    Library Clause 17)t
300 1015 M
(Issue Number:  17-011)t
300 1055 M
(Title:)t
450 1055 M
(         Library Defined in Terms of Templates)t
300 1095 M
(Section:)t
300 1135 M
(Status:        Open)t
300 1175 M
(Description:)t
450 1255 M
(NNI objects to the fact that the complete library has been defined in)t
450 1295 M
(terms of templates.  This makes it more difficult to use the library)t
450 1335 M
(without a complete and in-depth knowledge of the language.  A grow-path)t
450 1375 M
(from C to C++ is also not facilitated by the use of templates in the)t
450 1415 M
(library. Furthermore, it makes it impossible to implement the library)t
450 1455 M
(on older systems \(where templates might not be supported yet\) and on)t
450 1495 M
(smaller \(e.g. embedded\) systems \(where templates are not implemented to)t
450 1535 M
(save space\).)t
300 1615 M
(Resolution:)t
450 1695 M
(Take no action.)t
450 1775 M
(Templates are heavily used in the standard library because they solve)t
450 1815 M
(problems of internationalization and generic programming which were)t
450 1855 M
(otherwise intractable.  The pros and cons of template-based approaches)t
450 1895 M
(were debated at great length and for several years during the)t
450 1935 M
(development of the library, and the committee is satisfied that the)t
450 1975 M
(issues have been fully aired and carefully considered.)t
300 2055 M
(Requestor:     Netherlands)t
300 2095 M
(Owner:)t
300 2135 M
(Emails:)t
300 2175 M
(Papers:        95/0199 = N0799 Issue R20)t
300 2255 M
(<---------------------------------------------------------------------->)t
300 2335 M
(Work Group:    Library Clause 17)t
300 2375 M
(Issue Number:  17-012)t
300 2415 M
(Title:)t
450 2415 M
(         )t
657 2415 M
(Decouple Libraries)t
300 2455 M
(Section:       17)t
300 2495 M
(Status:        Open)t
300 2535 M
(Description:)t
450 2615 M
(The general structure of the libraries shall be revised.  In)t
450 2655 M
(particular, it is necessary to )t
1163 2655 M
(decouple libraries.  In the current)t
450 2695 M
(proposal, there are unacceptable cross and forward references between)t
450 2735 M
(libraries \(and sections\).  The order of introduction of libraries is)t
450 2775 M
(not adequate.)t
300 2855 M
(Resolution:)t
