(Issue Number:  17-013)t
300 935 M
(Title:)t
600 935 M
(  How will users access non-ISO C symbols using C++ headers?)t
300 975 M
(Section:       17.3.1.2, Etc.)t
300 1015 M
(Status:        Open)t
300 1055 M
(Description:)t
300 1135 M
(It seems that the intent of the draft 26-September-1995 Standard is to require)t
300 1175 M
(C++ Standard library vendors to provide two sets of the 18 headers containing)t
300 1215 M
(C Standard library facilities \(as defined by ISO C and Amendment 1\). One set)t
300 1255 M
(named <)t
461 1255 M
(cname> is provided to give C++ Standard library  users access to ISO C)t
300 1295 M
(features in the namespace std.  This includes exactly 54 standard macros, 45)t
300 1335 M
(standard values, 19 standard types, 2 structures, and 208 standard functions)t
300 1375 M
(\(17.3.1.1\). The C++ <)t
783 1375 M
(cname> headers do contain  some differences from ISO C)t
300 1415 M
(but these are detailed in the draft. In line with this footnote 139 to section)t
300 1455 M
(17.3.4.2 \(Restrictions on macro definitions\) states that a global function can)t
300 1495 M
(not be declared by the implementation as  taking additional default arguments.)t
300 1535 M
(The other set, named <)t
806 1535 M
(name.h> is  provided for compatibility only and is)t
300 1575 M
(deprecated C++ functionality \(D.4\). The draft states that C++ provided)t
300 1615 M
(<)t
323 1615 M
(name.h> headers should only include their corresponding C++ <)t
1726 1615 M
(cname> header)t
300 1655 M
(followed by an explicit using-declaration for each name placed in the Standard)t
300 1695 M
(library namespace by the header  \(17.3.4.1, D.4\).)t
300 1775 M
(This scheme raises the issue of how C++ users access non-ISO C symbols through)t
300 1815 M
(the C++ header files.   Non-ISO C symbols include symbols placed in these)t
300 1855 M
(headers by the various ISO POSIX standards, X/Open CAE Specification, Issue 4,)t
300 1895 M
(Version 2, as well as vendor specific extensions. In addition it adds)t
300 1935 M
(confusion by supporting two sets of ISO C headers \(one set provided by C++ as)t
300 1975 M
(per D.4 and one set provided by the C language\).)t
300 2055 M
(There are many examples of commonly used ISO C extensions in the 18 C++)t
300 2095 M
(Standard library headers provided for C library compatibility which would not)t
300 2135 M
(be available to C++ users \(even in the global namespace\) if <)t
1703 2135 M
(cname> and)t
300 2175 M
(<)t
323 2175 M
(name.h> C++ headers do not allow extensions.  Use of the Standard C library)t
300 2215 M
(localtime\(\), )t
599 2215 M
(ctime\(\), )t
806 2215 M
(strftime\(\) and )t
1151 2215 M
(mktime\(\) functions whose prototypes will)t
300 2255 M
(exist in the C++ supplied <)t
921 2255 M
(ctime> and <)t
1197 2255 M
(time.h> headers offer one  example.)t
300 2295 M
(Often the )t
530 2295 M
(tzset\(\) function \(defined by the ISO POSIX  standards as well as the)t
300 2335 M
(X/Open CAE Specification, Issue 4, Version 2\)  is used in conjunction with the)t
300 2375 M
(time routines to set and access  )t
1059 2375 M
(timezone conversion information.  Since)t
300 2415 M
(tzset\(\) is not defined by  ISO C, it would not be provided by the C++ Standard)t
300 2455 M
(library.  A C++  user including <)t
1059 2455 M
(ctime> and/or a C++ version of <)t
1795 2455 M
(time.h> would)t
300 2495 M
(not  have access to the prototype for )t
1174 2495 M
(tzset\(\).)t
300 2575 M
(Similarly consider the confusion which arises in the  following  example of a)t
300 2615 M
(C++ program which includes a C library header say  )t
1473 2615 M
(newlibc.h which includes)t
300 2655 M
(time.h in order to make visible the POSIX symbol CLK_TCK.  If the C++ Standard)t
300 2695 M
(library headers of the form <)t
967 2695 M
(name.h> do not  provide access to ISO C)t
300 2735 M
(extensions then what will be visible to the C++ program including )t
1818 2735 M
(newlibc.h?)t
300 2775 M
(Will )t
415 2775 M
(newlibc.h include  the C++ Standard library version of  )t
1703 2775 M
(time.h which only)t
300 2815 M
(includes <)t
530 2815 M
(ctime> which does not define CLK_TCK? Or will it include the)t
300 2855 M
(existing C library header which contains the symbol?)t
