(Resolution:)t
300 335 M
(A set of changes to Sections 17.3 \(Library-wide requirements\) and )t
1818 335 M
(subclause)t
300 375 M
(D.4 \(Standard C library headers\) of the draft 26-September-1995 C++ Standard)t
300 415 M
(are proposed to clarify the use of non-ISO C extensions  in the C++ headers)t
300 455 M
(for C library facilities.  The proposed changes follow:)t
300 535 M
(1.  Section 17.3.1.2 \(Headers\) paragraph 4 states:)t
300 615 M
(    Except as noted in Clauses 18 through 27, the contents of each)t
300 655 M
(    header )t
553 655 M
(cname shall be the same as that of the corresponding header)t
300 695 M
(    )t
392 695 M
(name.h, as specified in ISO C \(Clause 7\) or Amendment 1, \(Clause 7\),)t
300 735 M
(    as appropriate.  In this C++ Standard library, however, the declarations)t
300 775 M
(    and definitions are within namespace scope \(3.3.5\) of the namespace)t
300 815 M
(    std.)t
300 895 M
(    Proposed Wording:)t
300 975 M
(    Except as noted in Clauses 18 through 27, the contents of each)t
300 1015 M
(    header )t
553 1015 M
(cname shall be the same as that of the corresponding header)t
300 1055 M
(    )t
392 1055 M
(name.h, as specified in ISO C \(Clause 7\) or Amendment 1, \(Clause 7\),)t
300 1095 M
(    as appropriate.  In this C++ Standard library, however, the declarations)t
300 1135 M
(    and definitions from ISO C \(Clause 7\) or Amendment 1 \(Clause 7\) are)t
300 1175 M
(    within namespace scope \(3.3.5\) of the namespace std.)t
300 1255 M
(    Rationale:)t
300 1335 M
(    This change acknowledges the existence of non-ISO C symbols in)t
300 1375 M
(    the 18 C++ Standard library headers for C library facilities.  It)t
300 1415 M
(    specifies that ISO C declarations and definitions are provided within)t
300 1455 M
(    namespace scope of the namespace std.  Non-ISO C symbols may be)t
300 1495 M
(    provided but not within the namespace scope of the namespace std.)t
300 1575 M
(2.  Section 17.3.4.1 \(Headers\) paragraph 2 line 1 states:)t
300 1655 M
(    -- The C headers \(.h form, described in Annex D, D.4\) shall include)t
300 1695 M
(    only their corresponding C++ header, as described above \(17.3.1.2\))t
300 1775 M
(    Proposed Wording:)t
300 1855 M
(    Strike this section as it is already covered in section D.4 which)t
300 1895 M
(    is discussed below.)t
300 1975 M
(    Rationale:)t
300 2055 M
(    Keep the discussion of the C++ Standard library <)t
1519 2055 M
(name.h> headers)t
300 2095 M
(    in one place.)t
300 2175 M
(3.  Section 17.3.4.2 \(Restrictions on macro definitions\) Footnote 139 states:)t
300 2255 M
(    A global function cannot be declared by the implementation as)t
300 2295 M
(    taking additional default arguments.  Also, the use of masking)t
300 2335 M
(    macros for function signatures declared in  C headers is)t
300 2375 M
(    disallowed, notwithstanding the latitude granted in )t
1588 2375 M
(subclause)t
300 2415 M
(    7.1.7 of the C Standard.  The use of a masking macro can often)t
300 2455 M
(     be replaced by defining the function signature as inline.)t
300 2535 M
(    Proposed Wording:)t
300 2615 M
(    A global function in the std namespace cannot be declared by the)t
300 2655 M
(    implementation as taking additional default arguments.  Also, the use)t
300 2695 M
(    of masking macros for function signatures declared in  C headers is)t
300 2735 M
(    disallowed in the std namespace, notwithstanding the latitude granted)t
300 2775 M
(    in )t
461 2775 M
(subclause 7.1.7 of the C Standard.  The use of a masking macro can)t
300 2815 M
(    often be replaced by defining the function signature as inline.)t
300 2895 M
(    Rationale:)t
